snippet.title: Travel Agency Open Source CMS
snippet.description: An Open Source CMS in PHP to manage a travel agency for free

snippet.title: Open Travel Data
snippet.description: Framework (scripts, configuration, code) to build free and public services around travel and leisure data. That project makes an extensive use of already existing data sources such as Geonames and dbPedia, and adds some glue around those (eg, links).

snippet.title: OTA Tools (Open Travel Alliance)
snippet.description: A set of software tools useful for building, testing, and exercising web services (and other interfaces) for the travel industry which comply with the specifications of the Open Travel Alliance (OTA). This project is initiated by members of the OTA.

snippet.title: Solarex - Travel and Explore the Galaxy
snippet.description: Solarex is a space traveling, trading and prospecting game built upon a stellar system generator. There is a galaxy full of stellar systems with all sorts of treasures to explore - so enter your spaceship, buy some fuel and head off!

snippet.title: simutrans
snippet.description: Simutrans is a transport simulation game. Planes, ships, trains, trams, trucks, busses, or monorails are at your disposal. But factories have contracts and passengers will only travel to their own destinations. Many graphic sets (paks) are available.

snippet.title: Fabled Lands App
snippet.description: An adaptation of the Fabled Lands gamebook series: travel through a fantastic world, amassing skill, wealth, and fame, while avoiding sudden death. Presents the complete text to preserve the spirit of the original.
